R Notebook on CNP GO-POPCORN Dataset for reproducing figures, tables, and summary for publication in Scientific Data

Tatsuro Tanioka, University of California Irvine, tatsurt@uci.edu

2022-08-04

Files Required:

  1. “Data” contains POM data for GO-POPCORN ver 1 and ver 2
  • 1.1 “Data/CNP_data_DRYAD_edit_2.csv” = GO-POPCORN ver 1 available for download from https://doi.org/10.5061/dryad.d702p
  • 1.2 “Data/data_GOPOPCORN_ver2.csv” = GO-POPCORN ver 2 available for download from https://doi.org/10.5061/dryad.05qfttf5h
  • 1.3 “Data/Basin_Mask” Contains Regions info for each samples in ver 1 and ver 2 (0 = Land, 1 = Atlantic, including Mediterranean, 2 = Pacific, 3 = Indian, 4 = Arctic, 5 = Southern Ocean)

  1. “Figures” contains all the figures from the manuscript produced by running “analyze_gopopcorn_forSciData.Rmd”

  2. “Tables” contains all the Tables from the manuscript produced by running “analyze_gopopcorn_forSciData.Rmd”

  3. “Functions” contains extra R functions used to bin data by longitude and latitude.

# Function to Convert time to UCT
toDate <- function(year, month, day, hour, min) {
   ISOdate(year, month, day, hour, min, tz = "UCT")
}

toDate2 <- function(year, month, day) {
   ISOdate(year, month, day, tz = "UCT")
}

toNumerics <- function(Date) {
   stopifnot(inherits(Date, c("Date", "POSIXt")))
   day <- as.numeric(strftime(Date, format = "%d"))
   month <- as.numeric(strftime(Date, format = "%m"))
   year <- as.numeric(strftime(Date, format = "%Y"))
   list(year = year, month = month, day = day)
}

Read GO-POPCORN ver1 and clean them for consistent column names

# Version 1 of POM dataset (Martiny et al. 2014)
dataPOM_all_ver1_raw <- read.csv("Data/CNP_data_DRYAD_edit_2.csv", header = TRUE)
dataPOM_all_ver1_new <- dataPOM_all_ver1_raw 
dataPOM_all_ver1_new_ISO.DateTime.UTC <- toDate2(dataPOM_all_ver1_new$Year,
                                     dataPOM_all_ver1_new$Month,
                                     dataPOM_all_ver1_new$Day)
dataPOM_all_ver1_new_ISO.DateTime.UTC <- format(dataPOM_all_ver1_new_ISO.DateTime.UTC,
                                      format = "%Y-%m-%d")
dataPOM_all_ver1_new$ISO.DateTime.UTC <-dataPOM_all_ver1_new_ISO.DateTime.UTC

dataPOM_all_ver1_new <- dataPOM_all_ver1_new %>% replace_with_na(replace = list(POP.......µmol.L.1.= -9.999000e+03))
dataPOM_all_ver1_new <- dataPOM_all_ver1_new %>% replace_with_na(replace = list(POC..µmol.L.1.= -9999.0000000))
dataPOM_all_ver1_new <- dataPOM_all_ver1_new %>% replace_with_na(replace = list(PON..µmol.L.1.= -9.999000e+03))

dataPOM_all_ver1_new$POP <- dataPOM_all_ver1_new$POP.......µmol.L.1.*1000
dataPOM_all_ver1_new$PCODavg_uM <- rep(NA, nrow(dataPOM_all_ver1_new))
dataPOM_all_ver1 <- dataPOM_all_ver1_new %>% dplyr::select(Cruise = Dataset,
                                                           Latitude,
                                                           Longitude,
                                                           Depth = Depth..m.,
                                                           Month,
                                                           Day,
                                                           Year,
                                                           POCavg_uM = POC..µmol.L.1.,
                                                           PONavg_uM = PON..µmol.L.1.,
                                                           POPavg_nM = POP,
                                                           PCODavg_uM) %>% filter(abs(Longitude) < 180,abs(Latitude) < 90)
# Round Latitude and Longitude to 4dp
dataPOM_all_ver1[,'Latitude'] <- signif(dataPOM_all_ver1[,'Latitude'], digits = 4)
dataPOM_all_ver1[,'Longitude'] <- signif(dataPOM_all_ver1[,'Longitude'], digits = 4)

dataPOM_all_ver2_surface <- filter(data_GOPOPCORN_ver2, Depth <= 5)

# Bin surface data (top 5 m) to 1-by-1 deg and by 5-by-5 for version 1

                                  Cruise, 
                                  Latitude,
                                  Longitude,
                                  Depth,
                                  Month,
                                  Day,

                                  PONavg_uM,
                                  POPavg_nM,
                                  PCODavg_uM)

dataPOM_all_ver1_ver2_combined_surface_binned_1deg <- bin_data_ndeg_pomonly(drop_na(dataPOM_all_ver1_ver2_combined_surface,POCavg_uM, PONavg_uM,POPavg_nM), 
                                                                    ndeg = 1) %>% drop_na(Longitude, Latitude)

Add Region Information

0 = Land, 1 = Atlantic, including Mediterranean, 2 = Pacific, 3 = Indian, 4 = Arctic, 5 = Southern Ocean

dataPOM_all_ver1_surface_Basin_Mask <- read.csv("Data/Basin_Mask/dataPOM_ver1_basinonly.csv")
dataPOM_all_ver1_surface_binned_1deg_Basin_Mask <- read.csv("Data/Basin_Mask/dataPOM_ver1_binned_basinonly.csv")
dataPOM_all_ver2_surface_Basin_Mask <- read.csv("Data/Basin_Mask/dataPOM_ver2_basinonly.csv")
dataPOM_all_ver1_ver2_combined_surface_Basin_Mask <- read.csv("Data/Basin_Mask/dataPOM_ver1_ver2_combined_basinonly.csv")

dataPOM_all_ver1_surface$Region <- dataPOM_all_ver1_surface_Basin_Mask$Region
dataPOM_all_ver1_surface_binned_1deg$Region <- dataPOM_all_ver1_surface_binned_1deg_Basin_Mask$Region

dataPOM_all_ver2_surface_pomonly$Region <- dataPOM_all_ver2_surface_Basin_Mask$Region

dataPOM_all_ver1_ver2_combined_surface$Region <- dataPOM_all_ver1_ver2_combined_surface_Basin_Mask$Region
# Combine Versions 1&2 into a single dataframe for visualization later
dataPOM_all_ver1_surface  <- dataPOM_all_ver1_surface %>% mutate(Version = rep("Ver1", nrow(dataPOM_all_ver1_surface))) %>% mutate(Region = as.factor(Region), Version = as.factor(Version))
dataPOM_all_ver2_surface_pomonly  <- dataPOM_all_ver2_surface_pomonly %>% mutate(Version = rep("Ver2", nrow(dataPOM_all_ver2_surface_pomonly))) %>% mutate(Region = as.factor(Region), Version = as.factor(Version))
dataPOM_all_ver1_ver2_combined_surface <- rbind(dataPOM_all_ver1_surface,dataPOM_all_ver2_surface_pomonly) %>% mutate(Region = as.factor(Region), Version = as.factor(Version))
# Reorder region Factors 
dataPOM_all_ver1_ver2_combined_surface$Region <- factor(dataPOM_all_ver1_ver2_combined_surface$Region, levels = c('0','1','2','3','5','4'))

Calculating Median and IQR C:N:P:-O2

data_for_stats_vers2_surface <- drop_na(dataPOM_all_ver2_surface,
                                POCavg_uM,
                                PONavg_uM,
                                POPavg_nM)
data_for_stats_vers1_surface <- drop_na(dataPOM_all_ver1_surface,
                                POCavg_uM,
                                PONavg_uM,
                                POPavg_nM)

# Median C:N:P = 140:19:1 (Version 1)
# Median C:N:P:-O2 = 136:21:1, median -O2:C = 1.14 (Version 2)
medianCP_ver2 <- median(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$CP, na.rm = TRUE)
medianNP_ver2 <- median(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$NP, na.rm = TRUE)
medianCN_ver2 <- median(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$CN, na.rm = TRUE)
medianRQ_ver2 <- median(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$RQ, na.rm =TRUE)
medianO2P_ver2 <- median(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$O2_P, na.rm =TRUE)

medianCP_ver1 <- median(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$CP, na.rm = TRUE)
medianNP_ver1 <- median(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$NP, na.rm = TRUE)
medianCN_ver1 <- median(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$CN, na.rm = TRUE)

# Geometric means
geomeanCP_ver2 = exp(mean(log(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$CP[is.finite(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$CP)]), na.rm = TRUE))
geomeanNP_ver2 = exp(mean(log(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$NP[is.finite(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$NP)]), na.rm = TRUE))
geomeanCN_ver2 = exp(mean(log(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$CN[is.finite(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$CN)]), na.rm = TRUE))
geomeanRQ_ver2 = exp(mean(log(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$RQ[is.finite(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$RQ)]), na.rm = TRUE))
geomeanO2P_ver2 = exp(mean(log(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$O2_P[is.finite(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$O2_P)]), na.rm = TRUE))

geomeanCP_ver1 = exp(mean(log(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$CP[is.finite(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$CP)]), na.rm = TRUE))
geomeanNP_ver1 = exp(mean(log(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$NP[is.finite(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$NP)]), na.rm = TRUE))
geomeanCN_ver1 = exp(mean(log(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$CN[is.finite(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$CN)]), na.rm = TRUE))


# IQR C:P, N:P, C:N = 103.1; 12.7; 2.4 (Version 2)

IQR_NP_ver2 <- IQR(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$NP, na.rm = TRUE)
IQR_CN_ver2 <- IQR(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$CN, na.rm = TRUE)
IQR_RQ_ver2 <- IQR(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$RQ, na.rm =TRUE)
IQR_O2P_ver2 <- IQR(data_for_stats_vers2_surface$O2_P, na.rm =TRUE)

IQR_CP_ver1 <- IQR(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$CP, na.rm = TRUE)
IQR_NP_ver1 <- IQR(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$NP, na.rm = TRUE)
IQR_CN_ver1 <- IQR(data_for_stats_vers1_surface$CN, na.rm = TRUE)
